OL,7,FOfcom prefers the second option,
OL,8,Fwhich would maintain different rules
OL,9,Fregarding how often a programme on
OL,10,FITV 1, Channel 4, Channel 5, S4C and
OL,11,FSTV could be interrupted with adverts.
OL,13,FAlthough not its proposed approach,
OL,14,FOfcom says it "remains open to the
OL,15,Fpossibility of making no changes,
OL,16,Fkeeping the rules as they are".
OL,18,FAlongside considering existing
OL,19,Fquantitative research, Ofcom
OL,20,Fcommissioned new research to explore
OL,21,Fthe potential audience impact of
OL,22,Fchanges to its rules.
OL,3,COfcom consults on increasing ad time
OL,4,Con ITV 1 and other public service
OL,5,Cchannels
